summary: Jessica Millett prides herself on producing game-changing innovations and results. Connecting people, programs, and processes into something larger than themselves.  20 years of experience consulting in marketing, sales, new business development, and business management. Including the development of budgets, sales forecasting, coordination of planning teams and implementation plans.Among her significant previous positions, Jessica served on Organizational Development and Management Revitalization teams. Providing clients with superior leadership during critical transition phases. Implementing budget reductions, installing effective management information systems, and re-negotiation with existing contracted vendors.Outside of her professional portfolio, she is active in the local community. She has consulted many nonprofit organizations from startup to community outreach. President of an art community program for over three years. Jessica served on the Board of a program for underprivileged children. Currently, she is working on an advisory board for Valley of the Sun United Way.
